                "language":"eng",
                "stageNumber": 5,
                "sections": [
                    {
                        "_id": "5ecfb7681e0efa2517e44aae",
                        "title": "TVET Education",
                        "body": "<p>Having a quality and gender-transformative TVET curriculum alone is not enough to ensure that it&nbsp;will produce the desired results. It is also important to select and recruit the right people with the right (or potential) mindset to deliver the gender-transformative training in the classroom. This also requires human resource policies to ensure that there is a gender balance in teaching staff and administration.</p><p>TVET&nbsp;teaching staff will also be required to be further trained in youth education and empowerment with a gender-transformative approach, including sensitivity to the inclusion and exclusion of LGBT people, ethnic minorities or people with specific religious beliefs.</p>"
                    }
                ],
                "recommendedTools": [],
                "image": "levels/1591619143690201903-IDN-24-lpr.JPG",
                "description": "The key objective of technical education and vocational training is to equip young people with skills relevant to the labor market and prepare them for wage employment.\nIn this phase, there are 6 key steps that must be followed to develop a relevant and good quality technical and / or vocational education for young men and women.",
